channel.title: What the fuckalator?
channel.description:
Why does my PC load up slower than my shitty laptop that has 1gb of ram and a ~1GHz CPU. The PC runs games very well but that's mainly due to my sexy graphics card, loading up after logging in takes an age and a lot of programs generally lag.
Just wondering, this is what my PC has:

item.title: What the fuckalator?
item.dc:creator: @robocz033 robocz033
item.description:
@robocz033 wrote:

I’m pretty sure that I read on Microsoft’s website that you should reinstall XP every 6 months to ensure maximum operability. The registry is shit, BIOS is shit, basically Windows can fuck a monkey. If it weren’t so necessary for half the stuff I do, I’d ditch it real quick.

Honestly, I doubt that you can really do anything. It probably has a lot to do with bloated Windows functions and most likely “shortcuts” Windows uses to “speed up” processes. Just reinstall or upgrade to Win7. It’ll be a better experience in the end…

item.title: What the fuckalator?
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

[quote=“Speljohan, post:11, topic:328759”][quote author=Moparisthebest link=topic=425153.msg3122745#msg3122745 date=1265691783]

What OS? I’ll take a stab in the dark here and say XP. I’ve installed XP many times on my computer and found that everytime the computer gradually got slower and slower at starting, it’s just what happens with XP.

I’ve always noticed this too, the longer you have it installed the slower and slower it loads. It’s been like this since the original XP, before SP1. Don’t know if it’s related to the number of programs installed or what, but it can only be fixed as far as I know by re-installing the thing.
[/quote]I blame the system registry, it is an outdated piece of shit[/quote]
I just cleaned my registry and XP loaded 2X as fast.

Off-topic: Check your website.
